{Chapter 1B: Plan with dxe6. Here Black must always have in mind the maneuver
Nd7-e5, fighting for d4 square. And sometimes it is more important than the
weak pawn on d6, as this game shows!} 10. dxe6 (10. Re1 Rb8 (10... Re8 11. dxe6
Nxe6 12. Bc2 a6 13. Be3 Rb8 ({I could have continued like in the main game} 
13... Nd7 $5 14. Qxd6 ({But somehow this bothered me} 14. Ba4 $5 b5 15. cxb5
Nb6 16. Bb3 {and} Bxc3 {was not an easy decision,though after} 17. bxc3 axb5 {
White's advantage must be just tiny.}) 14... Ne5 15. Qxd8 Nxf3+ 16. gxf3 Rxd8
17. Kg2 b5 $5 $44 {with good play}) 14. a4 b6 15. Qd2 Nd7 {This sacrifice is
not the same one, the piece on d4 square is immediately exchanged.} (15... Bb7
$142 16. Rad1 Bf8) 16. Qxd6 Nd4 17. Bxd4 cxd4 18. Nd5 Bb7 19. Rad1 Ne5 20. Qxd8
Nxf3+ 21. gxf3 Rexd8 22. Bd3 a5 23. Bf1 g5 $14 {1-0 (61) Andreikin,D (2700)
-Chatalbashev,B (2550) Struga 2012}) 11. dxe6 Nxe6 12. Bf1 a6 {As the rook is
already placed on b8, this is the most logical plan.} 13. Be3 b5 $1 14. e5 (14.
cxb5 axb5 15. Bxb5 Nxe4 16. Nxe4 Rxb5 17. Nxd6 Rxb2 18. Nxc8 Qxc8 $15) 14...
dxe5 15. Qxd8 Rxd8 16. Nxe5 Bb7 $10 17. cxb5 axb5 18. Nxb5 {1-0 (40) Dreev,A 
(2615)-Damljanovic,B (2515) Manila 1990 CBM 019 [Stohl]} Nd5 $1) 10... Nxe6 11.
Be3 b6 (11... Nd7 12. Qd2 ({better is} 12. Be2 {with idea} Ne5 13. Nxe5 dxe5
14. Qxd8 Rxd8 15. Bg4 $14 {After the exchange of the white-squared bishop, no
matter for which piece,White will be left with his good one, compared to the
rather grim-looking Black bishop on g7.}) 12... Ne5 13. Be2 Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 Nd4
15. Bxd4 Bxd4 16. Bg4 Bxg4 17. hxg4 Qh4 18. Qe2 Rae8 19. Qf3 f5 20. exf5 gxf5
21. Nb5 fxg4 22. Qd5+ Rf7 23. Nxd6 Bxf2+ 24. Rxf2 Qxf2+ 25. Kh1 Re1+ 26. Rxe1
Qxe1+ 27. Kh2 Qh4+ 28. Kg1 Qf2+ 29. Kh2 Qf4+ 30. Kg1 Qd4+ 31. Qxd4 cxd4 {0-1 
(31) Gladyszev,O (2440)-Chatalbashev,B (2546) France 2004}) 12. Qd2 Bb7 13. Bc2
Nd7 $1 {Right timing.} 14. Qxd6 Ne5 15. Qxd8 Nxf3+ 16. gxf3 Raxd8 17. Rad1 Nd4
18. Bxd4 Bxd4 19. Rfe1 Ba6 20. Bd3 Rd7 21. Nd5 $6 Bxb2 22. Rb1 Bd4 23. Rb3 Bb7
24. Kg2 Bc6 25. Re2 Kg7 26. Rb1 Rb8 27. Ree1 Rdb7 28. Rb3 a6 29. Ra3 a5 30. Rb3
a4 31. Rbb1 b5 32. cxb5 Bxb5 33. Bc2 a3 34. Ne3 Ba6 35. Rxb7 Rxb7 36. Bb3 Rxb3
37. axb3 Bd3 0-1

