{Finally we will deal with a Modern Benoni type of position that comes after
White chooses cxd5. Certainly the fact that we manage b7-b5 is an achievement,
but it is not so simple. The knight on c7 stands passive, though his defensive
role is also important. Apart from protecting on b5, e4-e5 is also discouraged
by the hanging d5 pawn. Still, as we will see in the games, Black gets good
play when we activate it - either to c5 or after b5-b4 - to b5.} 10. Re1 (10.
Bg5 h6 11. Be3 exd5 12. cxd5 b5 13. Qd2 b4 14. Ne2 Re8 15. Ng3 Kh7 16. Qc2 Rb8
(16... a5 $5 {with idea Ba6} 17. Nd2 a4 18. Nc4 Ba6) 17. Nd2 (17. Bf4 $5 Qe7
18. Rfe1 Nd7) 17... Nd7 18. Nc4 Ba6 19. Rae1 (19. Nxd6 $4 Bxd3 20. Qxd3 Ne5)
19... Bxc4 20. Bxc4 Qh4 21. Bd3 Ne5 22. Be2 Nb5 23. Qd2 Nd4 24. Bxd4 cxd4 25.
Rc1 Re7 26. Kh1 Nd7 27. Bd3 Nc5 28. Bb1 a5 (28... b3 29. a3 Qg5 $1 $17) 29. Kh2
Rbe8 30. f4 Nd7 31. Rc6 Nf6 32. Rf3 Ng4+ 33. Kg1 Ne3 34. Bd3 Rd8 35. Nf1 h5 {
1/2 (35) Berczes,D (2520)-Sale,S (2400) Sibenik 2010}) 10... Rb8 11. Bg5 h6 12.
Be3 exd5 13. cxd5 b5 14. Qd2 Kh7 (14... b4 {I like more the immediate b5-b4.
Still the game is important, as White could also have played a2-a3 earlier,
when similar positions arise.}) 15. a3 a5 16. b4 axb4 17. axb4 Na6 (17... Nd7
18. Ra7) 18. bxc5 Nxc5 19. Bxc5 ({Some other tactical possibilities -} 19. Ra7
Qb6 20. Ra2 Bd7 21. e5 dxe5 22. Nxe5 b4 23. Na4 (23. Ra6 bxc3 24. Qxc3 Nxd5 25.
Rxb6 Nxc3 26. Bxc5 $11) 23... Bxa4 24. Rxa4 Nfe4 25. Bxe4 Nxe4 $11) 19... dxc5
20. e5 c4 (20... b4 $5 21. Na4 Nxd5 22. Nxc5 Qe7 $11) 21. exf6 Bxf6 22. Bc2 b4
23. Ne4 (23. Qf4 $5) 23... Bxa1 24. Rxa1 Bf5 (24... b3 $142 25. Bb1 Bf5 $13)
25. Qd4 b3 26. Nf6+ Qxf6 27. Qxf6 bxc2 28. Nd2 c3 29. Qxc3 Rfc8 30. Qd4 c1=Q+
31. Rxc1 Rxc1+ 32. Kh2 Rc2 33. Qa7 (33. Nf3 $142 $16) 33... Rxd2 {Conclusion:
In the Main Line the only plan, in my opinion, that poses some problems for
Black, is that with allowing b7-b5. Surprisingly it is not White's most
frequent choice,as most players go for a2-a4. But even if it happens - we are
not afraid and well prepared!} 1/2-1/2

