{Finally I want to show you the other possible plan - with Nbd7-e5. It is more
risky, but sometimes it works nice for Black - as in the following beautiful
game!} 9... Re8 10. O-O Nbd7 11. a4 Ne5 12. Qc2 (12. f4 $2 Neg4 13. Nc4 Nxe4
14. Bxg4 Bxg4 15. Qxg4 Bd4+ 16. Ne3 Nxc3 $17) ({In all these lines} 12. h3 {is
met by} g5 {Of course Black weakens his kingside, but manages to secure his
strong knight on e5.}) 12... Bg4 $5 13. f3 ({The other option} 13. Bxg4 Nfxg4
14. h3 Nf6 15. f4 Ned7 16. Nf3 Rc8 (16... c4 $1 17. Be3 a6 (17... Qa5) 18. Rfe1
Qa5) 17. Re1 c4 18. e5 dxe5 19. fxe5 Nxd5 20. Nxd5 Nxe5 21. Nxe5 Qxd5 22. Nf3
Rxe1+ 23. Nxe1 c3 24. b3 Qd4+ (24... Rd8 $1 $13) 25. Kf1 Rd8 26. Bg5 f6 27. Nf3
$16 {1-0 (45) Kozul,Z (2617)-Chatalbashev,B (2561)/Zagreb 2010/CBM 145}) 13...
Bd7 14. f4 $2 (14. Nc4 Nxc4 15. Bxc4 Nh5 16. g4 Bd4+ 17. Kh1 Ng7 18. Bf4 h5 19.
h3 (19. Bxd6 hxg4 20. fxg4 Bxg4 21. Nb5 a6 $13) 19... Qh4 20. Qh2 Be5 21. Bxe5
Rxe5 22. Bb5 Rd8 23. f4 Ree8 24. g5 a6 25. Bxd7 Rxd7 26. Qg2 Rde7 27. a5 Rf8
28. Kh2 f5 29. gxf6 Qxf6 30. Qg5 Qxg5 (30... Ref7 $11) 31. fxg5 Ref7 32. Rxf7
Rxf7 33. Kg2 h4 $6 34. Rf1 $16 {1-0 (44) Markus,R (2617)-Dvirnyy,D (2480)/Nova
Gorica SLO 2011/The Week in Chess 848}) 14... Neg4 15. Nc4 (15. Nf3 Qe7 16. Re1
Nxe4 17. Bd3 f5 18. Nxe4 fxe4 19. Rxe4 Qf8 $15) 15... Nxe4 $1 16. Nxe4 (16.
Bxg4 Nxc3 17. Bxd7 Ne2+ $17) 16... Bd4+ 17. Kh1 Nxh2 $1 18. Ng5 (18. g3 Nxf1
19. Bxf1 Bf5 20. Bd3 (20. Ncxd6 Bxe4+ 21. Nxe4 Qxd5 22. Bd3 c4 $19) (20. Ncd2
Qe7 21. Bd3 Qf8 $19) 20... Bxe4+ 21. Bxe4 f5 22. Bf3 Re1+ 23. Kg2 Qf8 $19)
18... Nxf1 19. Bxf1 Re1 20. Nd2 Qf8 21. Ra3 Qh6+ 22. Rh3 Bxh3 23. Nxh3 Qh5 24.
Kh2 Qd1 0-1

